The '''National Hostosian Congress''' ({{lang-es|Congreso Nacional Hostosiano}}, CNH) was a small [[left-wing politics|left-wing]] and [[Puerto Rican independence movement|pro-independence]] organization in [[Puerto Rico]]. Led by [[Héctor L. Pesquera]], many of its members were formerly involved in the [[Puerto Rican Socialist Party]]. In 2004, the CNH joined with the [[Nuevo Movimiento Independentista Puertorriqueño|New Puerto Rican Independence Movement]] to form the [[Hostosian National Independence Movement]] (MINH).

