{{about|the Mexican Ministry of Economy|the dicastery of the Roman Curia|Secretariat for the Economy (Holy See)}} {{Infobox government agency | name = Office for Economic Affairs | native_name = Secretaría de Economía | native_name_a = | native_name_r = | type = | seal = | seal_width = | seal_caption = | logo = SE logo 2012.svg | logo_width = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | formed = 1917 | preceding1 = Office for Commerce and Industrial Development | jurisdiction = | headquarters = Av. Insurgentes Sur 1940, Florida, 01030 [[Mexico City]] Mexico | coordinates = {{coord|19|21|9.47|N|99|11|8.46|W|type:landmark|display=inline}} | employees = | budget = | chief1_name = [[Ildefonso Guajardo Villarreal]] | chief1_position = Director for Economic Affairs | chief2_name = | chief2_position = | chief3_name = | chief3_position = | chief4_name = | chief4_position = | chief5_name = | chief5_position = | chief6_name = | chief6_position = | chief7_name = | chief7_position = | chief8_name = | chief8_position = | chief9_name = | chief9_position = | parent_department = | child1_agency = National Meteorological Centre | child2_agency = Federal Competition Board | child3_agency = Federal Commission on Regulatory Reform | child5_agency = Mining Development Trust Fund | child6_agency = Mexican Industrial Property Board | child7_agency = Federal Consumer's Advocate | child8_agency = [[ProMéxico]] | child9_agency = Mexican Geological Service | website = [http://www.economia.gob.mx/en www.economia.gob.mx/en] }}
In [[Mexico]], the '''Office for Economic Affairs''' ([[Spanish Language|Spanish:]] ''Secretaría de Economía''; abbreviated "SE") is the [[Ministry (government department)|government department]] in charge of matters related to the economy. The Officer for Economic Affairs is a member of the [[Mexican Executive Cabinet|federal executive cabinet]] appointed by the [[President of Mexico|President of the Republic]].
Until 2000 the name of the Office for Economic Affairs was the ''Office for Commerce and Industrial Development'' ''(SCFI)'' but that name was changed when [[Vicente Fox]] acceded to the Presidency.
The {{As of|2010|alt=current}} Director of Economic Affairs is Ildefonso Guajardo Villarreal.
